abstract: British heritage group announces discovery of 600-year-old sunken ship it believes was from fleet of Henry V; says ship is likely a vessel called Holigost, which was active in English king's 15th-century wars with France.
lead_paragraph: Historic England, a heritage organization, discovered what it says is a 600-year-old wreck in the mud of a river near Southampton.

headline.main: British Group Says It Found Holigost, a Ship in Henry V’s Fleet
headline.print_headline: British Say They Found Henry V Wreck
